external_knowledge:
- "Top-performing seasons" refers to seasons with the highest win percentages within their respective season types;
- "Highest-scoring games" refers to games with the most points scored within the top-performing seasons;
- "Win percentage greater than 50%" means the team won more than half of their games in the season.

- "season_id" is a unique identifier for each season;
- "total_wins" represents the number of games won in the season;
- The metaphor "the grand theater of sports" refers to the competitive nature of the games;
- "the triumph of victory" and "the curtain of success" are poetic ways to describe winning a game.

sql:
SELECT year, total_games 
FROM seasons 
WHERE season_id = (SELECT MAX(season_id) FROM seasons);

